scam_incident_description:
I saw an ad for discounted food items on Facebook posted by 'brittanymartinez'. The seller was promoting the sale of durians.
Upon clicking the link (https://www.deals4u-7347.shop/durians) in the post, I was redirected to a site requesting my my card credentials to complete the purchase. 
After submitting my details, I received an SMS requesting to key in my Youtrip login code. I subsequently received an SMS that there had been a log in to my account from another device. 
Later, an unauthorized transaction was made to a CIMB. The transaction is as follows:

When I denied knowledge of such transactions, the call was transferred to another individual named Inspector Thomas Lee via WhatsApp, claiming to be from the Monetary Authority of Singapore. 
They accused me of involvement in legal investigation and demanded that I transfer my bank funds to a "safety account" to assist with the investigations. 
Inspector Thomas Lee showed me his warrant card during the process and I believed him. I complied and transferred the funds, resulting in the following transaction:
A transaction of $3915.32 was made to MAYBANK account 52380552 on 2025-05-16.
I later realized I had been scammed when the individuals became uncontactable. I subsequently verified the situation with the bank and Singapore Police Force through official channels and 
there were no records of Jeremy Tan and Inspector Thomas Lee.
